{
  "texts": [
    "For arbitrary feature vector x, let f be the feature representation generated by model param- eters θ(T), i.e., vector f is the input to the model's last linear layer given input x.",
    "Then the representer point influence estimator for a multilayer model is",
    "Treating as constants feature representation dimension |f| and the overhead to calculate (ŷ i,y i) ŷ, estimating the entire training set's representer point influence only requires calculating n dot products.",
    "This only takes O(n) time and O(n + p) space with no additional storage requirements.",
    "Representer point's primary advantage is its theoretical and computational simplicity."
  ]
}